WHO   — TURBOGRAFX-16 · PC ENGINE — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown
WHAT  — NEC and Hudson's tiny machine punched far above its size: an 8-bit CPU core paired with a 16-bit video chip, a huge sprite budget, and a credit-card game format. It was first to market with a CD-ROM add-on, opening the door to the multimedia generation.
